##
## UPGRADING
##
## Jeffrey Hobbs, jhobbs@cs.uoregon.edu
## 19 December 1996
##

For those users who became familiar with Roland King's version of tkTable,
or Ellson et al's Tk4 upgrade to it, you'll may want a little assistance in
in transitioning to this new and better version.  If version 1.0+ is new to
you, just read the man page (or HTML equivalent).

The format of this upgrade document is to define the area of the change and
the show the old code and its new equivalent.  Comments may follow for
seemingly obscure changes.  Not all the new features are listed (we just
want you to be able to upgrade old code), so don't forget to look through
the documentation for new procedures that will make previous tasks easier.

METHOD CHANGES:

* whatcell
 [old]	.table whatcell x y
 [new]	.table index @x,y

* whereis
 [old]	.table whereis row col
 [new]	.table bbox index

* leftcol, toprow, bottomrow, rightcol
 [old]	.table leftcol|toprow|bottomrow|rightcol ?rowOrCol?
 [new]	.table index topleft|bottomright ?row|col?
	.table [xy]view row|col ;# This will set the top|left cell

* rindex, cindex
 [old]	.table [rc]index index
 [new]	.table index index row|col

* setcell
 [old]	.table setcell
 [new]	.table curselection
## This returns _all_ selected cells, like the listbox method.
## The "active" index represents the active cell (that which is currently
## being edited).

* batch
 [old]	.table batch on|off
 [new]	.table configure -batchmode on|off

* drawmode
 [old]	.table drawmode mode
 [new]	.table configure -drawmode mode

* editmode
 [old]	.table editmode mode
 [new]	.table configure -state normal|disabled
  &&	.table configure -autoclear on|off

* flash
 [old]	.table flash on|off
 [new]	.table configure -flashmode on|off
 [old]	.table flash tag tagName
 [new]	"flash" is a permanent tag configurable style
 [old]	.table flash timeout arg
 [new]	.table configure -flashtime arg

* getheight, getwidth
 [old]	.table getheight row
 [new]	.table height row
## vice versa for getwidth

* height, width
 [old]	.table height {row height}
 [new]	.table height row height ?row height ...?
## vice versa for width

* insert
 [old]	.table insert index value
 [new]	.table insert active index value
## insert && delete where changed to allow the addition of the
## row/col insert/delete routines

* delete
 [old]	.table delete index ?index?
 [new]	.table delete active index ?index?

* colstretch, rowstretch
 [old]	.table rowstretch mode
 [new]	.table configure -rowstretch mode

* tag
 [old]	.table tag celltag tagName {row col}
 [new]	.table tag celltag tagName index

OPTION CHANGES:

* -procrowtag, -proccoltag
 [old]	.table configure -procrowtag cmd
 [new]	.table configure -rowtagcommand cmd

* -cursorbg
 [old]	.table configure -cursorbg
 [new]	.table configure -insertbackground

* -rowtitle, -coltitle
 [old]	.table configure -rowtitle number
 [new]	.table configure -titlerows number
## Why? because -*title was more misleading than -title*

MISC CHANGES:

* "Title" tag
 [old]	.table configure tag Title ...
 [new]	.table configure tag title ...

* Default color fixes
